    "ELECTRICITY TARIFFS FOR KENYAN MSMEs — EPRA/KPLC GUIDE 2024/2025 Energy and Petroleum Regulatory Authority (EPRA) & Kenya Power (KPLC) Source: EPRA approved tariffs, effective July 2024 === OVERVIEW === Kenya Power (KPLC) distributes electricity to 9.6 million+ customers. EPRA sets and regulates all electricity tariffs in Kenya. MSMEs fall under different tariff categories depending on consumption. === TARIFF CATEGORIES FOR MSMEs === 1. SMALL COMMERCIAL 1 (SC1) — Very small businesses - Usage: U",
    ". === TARIFF CATEGORIES FOR MSMEs === 1. SMALL COMMERCIAL 1 (SC1) — Very small businesses - Usage: Under 100 kWh/month - Examples: Small kiosks, hair salons, phone charging shops - Rate 2024/25: KSh 12.23 per unit (before taxes) - Fixed charge: KSh 150/month 2. SMALL COMMERCIAL 2 (SC2) — Small businesses - Usage: 100–300 kWh/month - Examples: Small restaurants, tailoring shops, small offices - Rate 2024/25: KSh 16.45 per unit - Fixed charge: KSh 300/month 3. SMALL COMMERCIAL 3 (SC3) — Medium-sma",
    "e 2024/25: KSh 16.45 per unit - Fixed charge: KSh 300/month 3. SMALL COMMERCIAL 3 (SC3) — Medium-small businesses - Usage: 300–1,000 kWh/month - Examples: Welding workshops, bakeries, small factories - Rate 2024/25: KSh 19.08 per unit - TOU (off-peak) rate: KSh 9.54 per unit (50% saving!) - Fixed charge: KSh 500/month 4. BULK SMALL COMMERCIAL — Growing businesses - Usage: 1,000–15,000 kWh/month - Examples: Laundromats, medium bakeries, cold storage - Rate 2024/25: KSh 18.50 per unit - TOU rate:",
    "Examples: Laundromats, medium bakeries, cold storage - Rate 2024/25: KSh 18.50 per unit - TOU rate: KSh 9.25 per unit - Demand charge: KSh 300 per kVA 5. COMMERCIAL & INDUSTRIAL 1 (CI1) — Larger businesses - Usage: Over 15,000 kWh/month - Rate 2024/25: KSh 13.74 per unit - TOU rate: KSh 6.87 per unit - Demand charge: KSh 1,100 per kVA === SPECIAL JUA KALI TARIFF === KPLC confirmed: Jua Kali sector businesses qualify for SPECIAL TARIFF - Small commercial, lifeline and ordinary tariffs for Jua Kal",
    "businesses qualify for SPECIAL TARIFF - Small commercial, lifeline and ordinary tariffs for Jua Kali - Rates are LOWER than domestic tariffs - Purpose: Support job creation in informal sector === ELECTRICITY BILL COMPONENTS === Your electricity bill includes: 1. Energy Charge — cost per kWh consumed 2. Fuel Cost Charge (FCC) — varies monthly with fuel prices 3. Foreign Exchange Adjustment — varies with KSh/USD rate 4. Inflation Adjustment — adjusted twice per year 5. WARMA Levy — KSh 0.05 per k",
    "s with KSh/USD rate 4. Inflation Adjustment — adjusted twice per year 5. WARMA Levy — KSh 0.05 per kWh for hydropower 6. Rural Electrification Levy — for rural connections 7. VAT (16%) — on total bill amount === TIME OF USE (TOU) RATES === TOU rates allow businesses to pay much less by using electricity at off-peak times: - Peak hours (6am–10pm): Full rate applies - Off-peak hours (10pm–6am): ~50% of daytime rate BEST FOR: Bakeries, cold storage, laundries, any business that can work at night ==",
    "of daytime rate BEST FOR: Bakeries, cold storage, laundries, any business that can work at night === HOW TO CONNECT YOUR BUSINESS TO KPLC === New Connection Procedure: 1. Visit kplc.co.ke or go to nearest KPLC office 2. Fill connection application form 3. Pay connection fees (varies by distance from grid) 4. KPLC installs meter within 30 days Documents Required: - National ID / Passport - KRA PIN certificate - Business permit / license - Title deed or landlord consent letter - Electrical instal",
    "certificate - Business permit / license - Title deed or landlord consent letter - Electrical installation inspection certificate Connection Costs: - Within 200m of existing grid: Standard connection fee - Beyond 200m: Extension costs apply (can be significant) - Rural connections: May qualify for KOSAP subsidies === ENERGY SAVING TIPS FOR MSMEs === 1. Switch to LED lighting — saves 60-80% on lighting costs 2. Use TOU tariff — run heavy machinery at night 3. Install solar panels — reduces grid d",
    "ting costs 2. Use TOU tariff — run heavy machinery at night 3. Install solar panels — reduces grid dependency 4. Energy audit — EPRA offers free energy audits for businesses 5. Efficient equipment — look for Kenya Energy Star labels === USEFUL CONTACTS === - Kenya Power customer care: *977# (toll-free on Safaricom) - Online account: selfservice.kplc.co.ke - EPRA complaints: epra.go.ke - Emergency line: 0703 070 707",
