    "gle–phase service. Large commercial and industrial customers have either two-phase or three–phase service. PLANNED ELECTRIC OUTAGE: An interruption of service to electric lines to permit work that cannot be performed while the lines are live with electric current. Whenever possible, affected customers are notified beforehand. POWER: The time rate of using electric energy, usually expressed in kilowatts. POWER GRID: A network of power lines and associated equipment used to transmit and distribute",
