    "level and beyond Its goal is real-time adjustment to changing loads, generation, and failure conditions of the distribution system, usually without operator intervention Base Load This is the minimum amount of power that a utility or distribution company must make available to its customers, or the amount of power required to meet minimum demands based on customer requirements Billing A charge applied to an electricity customer for energy reserved or made available explicitly for that customer T",
