    "vernments are in- charge of all roads system development and to determine the appropriate (rural and Urban) in classes D,E, F and G. jurisdictional responsibility for different roads. It is also used as a guide for developing design standards for various types of roads and for fiscal planning. Quick infobytes 5 How does KWS tie into road maintenance? The Board allocates one per cent of the monies from construction equipment and supervision vehicles the RMLF to the Kenya Wildlife Service for road",
