    "ate will investigate and review all performance aspects of the Urban & Park Roads to identify and express an independent opinion on their status and achievement expected outcomes including whether safety is integrated in all phases of planning, design, construction, operation and maintenance of road infrastructure and make recommendations as necessary to render projects management complaint, more efficient, cost effective and transparent Policy & Planning Directorate Policy & Planning Directorat",
    "efficient, cost effective and transparent Policy & Planning Directorate Policy & Planning Directorate is established pursuant to the Kenya Roads Board Act of 1999 Sections 6(1), 6(2), a, b, d, e, f, g, 19, 20, 21, 24, 25 The Directorate comprises of three departments namely: Policy & Research department, Road Management System (RMS) & Geo-informatics department, and Corporate Planning & Strategy department The Directorate’s responsibilities include: 1 Coordinate and monitor the implementation of",
    "epartment The Directorate’s responsibilities include: 1 Coordinate and monitor the implementation of road maintenance policies and strategies for effective management of the road network Coordinate preparation of RMLF ceilings for Road Authorities Coordinate the consolidation of APRP Review the Road Classification system and Roads Register Maintain and update the Road Inventory and Condition database Road Inventory and Condition Survey (RICS) is carried out every 5 years to monitor the changes i",
    "ase Road Inventory and Condition Survey (RICS) is carried out every 5 years to monitor the changes in the road inventory and conditions since the last RICS and thereby demonstrate the outcomes of road infrastructure funds (both for development and maintenance) The Directorate is currently carrying out RICS 2022 – 2023 that commenced in January 2022 and is expected to end November 2023 Coordinate and initiate development of Roads Sub-sector Investment Programme (RSIP) RSIP is a medium-term plan w",
    "nd initiate development of Roads Sub-sector Investment Programme (RSIP) RSIP is a medium-term plan which outlines road development and maintenance priorities RSIP covers the entire National Road Network and all types of interventions (ranging from Routine Maintenance to new construction) • 1st RSIP (2010-2015) prepared in 2011, expired in June 2015 • 2nd RSIP (2018-2022) is in place and shall expire December 2022 • 3rd RSIP (2023 – 2027) being developed 7 Promote road related Research and Develo",
    "re December 2022 • 3rd RSIP (2023 – 2027) being developed 7 Promote road related Research and Development in roads sub-sector The Directorate initiates and implements road related research programs and studies, coordinates innovations relating to maintenance, rehabilitation and development of the road network in Kenya In FY 2022/23, the directorate is undertaking research on “Causes of fissures on roads in Kenya: Case study of Maai Mahiu – Narok Road” in collaboration with the University of Nair",
    "roads in Kenya: Case study of Maai Mahiu – Narok Road” in collaboration with the University of Nairobi Coordinate implementation of Roads 2000 strategy The Roads 2000 strategy is a method of road development and management that ensures optimum utilisation and development of locally available resources where technically and economically feasible and in a socially responsive manner The Directorate develops a Roads 2000 Strategy every 5 years and monitors its implementation quarterly Provide techn",
    "develops a Roads 2000 Strategy every 5 years and monitors its implementation quarterly Provide technical support for Road Agencies and County Governments in road maintenance 10 Automation of the Board’s processes in collaboration with other directorates Currently, the directorate is automating the Annual Public Road Programme (APRP) and Cost Estimation Manual (CEM) for effective planning and reporting of the programs funded by the Board Road Safety Mainstreaming The Directorate coordinates road",
    "ting of the programs funded by the Board Road Safety Mainstreaming The Directorate coordinates road safety mainstreaming activities In FY 2021/22, the Board executed a collaboration framework with NTSA to reduce fatalities and injuries resulting from road accidents Leadership in the development, implementation and review of directorate’s annual work plans The Directorate also provides leadership in the development, implementation and review of directorate’s annual work plans to ensure that they",
